records.addlTxt:
Defendant Dustin J Brandt in court with attorney Andrew Charles Ladd.  Kristi J Gordon appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State files Information.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Counts 1, 3 and 4 are dismissed and read-in.  Court conducts plea colloquy with defendant.  State makes sentencing recommendation.  Defense makes sentencing recommendation.  Defendant makes statement.  

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

COUNT 2

6 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 4 days)
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION

TERM OF PROBATION:  3 YEAR(S)

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.'s; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed;
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions;
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling;
*No contact with:  victims or businesses listed in the complaint;
*Not to possess any personal identification information other than own.  

RESTITUTION:  $1,078.07 already paid

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (apply cash bail; refund balance to poster);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (apply cash bail; refund balance to poster);
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.

CONDITION TIME: 90 days, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
